Direct Known Subclasses:
GeoCodeExtension
public class BaseGeoCodeExtension
extends BaseLayerExtension
implements GeoCodeExtension

This implementation of GeoCodeExtension can be used to define a GeoCode LayerExtension for a particular FeatureLayer. It provides support for GeoCode Styles defined within properties files, but it does not provide support for actually performing a geocode operation - this must be supplied by a subclass. However, you can still use this helper class if you want to author a geocode service.

setGeocodeField

public void setGeocodeField(int index,
                            String field)
Sets a dataset field, that corresponds with a style definition tag. Note: You must associate a dataset field with each and every definition tag of the current style before you can save the geocode definition

Parameters:
index - the index of the corresponding definition tag
field - the name of the Field to be associated
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if field is null, or if field is not defined in the associated Layer
ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException - if the index is invalid
NullPointerException - if there is no associated GeoCodeStyle - it needs to be set using setStyle
